          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value based on the input parameters provided. This function is designed to calculate a specific period within a 24-hour cycle, for scheduling or time-based calculations. The function's name shows that it performs a modulo operation with 24, which is commonly used to wrap around values within a 24-hour format."
